The paper deals with the problem of maximizing the number of crossings in a graph drawing, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). It also involves graph theory (cs.DM) and complexity theory (cs.CC), as the authors prove hardness results for computing the maximum crossing number. The paper may also be relevant to the sub-fields of discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.GT), as it deals with properties of graphs and their drawings.
